Use rules for all websites built by Trendtactics Digital using Cursor.

autoAttach: true

Write clean, maintainable, and scalable code

Follow SOLID principles

Emphasize component-driven, modular development

Prefer functional and declarative programming patterns

Practice type safety and static analysis (TypeScript preferred)

Code Style

Use tabs for indentation

Use single quotes for strings

Omit semicolons unless required

Space after keywords and before parentheses

Limit lines to 80 characters

Use strict equality (===)

Comment sections clearly (e.g., <!-- HERO SECTION -->)

Project Structure & File Output

All builds must use HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript (React optional)

Use TailwindCSS unless otherwise specified

Structure: /index.html /about.html /contact.html /blog.html /blog-post.html /library.html (if eBooks) /courses.html, /course-detail.html, /student-dashboard.html (if LMS) /css/, /js/, /images/, /fonts/, /ebooks/ send.php robots.txt sitemap.xml privacy.html terms.html README.md

Design & UI/UX

Responsive and mobile-first is mandatory

Use flexible layouts: Hero-first, Grid, Bento, Z-pattern, One-page Scroll

Use Google Fonts depending on site type:

Bold: Poppins, Inter, Montserrat

Blogs: Lora, Playfair, Merriweather

Agencies: IBM Plex Sans, Raleway, Nunito

Ecommerce: Manrope, Ubuntu, Work Sans

Portfolios: Space Grotesk, Figtree, Rubik


Include dark mode toggle by default

Security & Accessibility

Sanitize user input (e.g., DOMPurify)

Use semantic HTML with ARIA labels where necessary

Ensure keyboard navigability

Maintain contrast ratios for readability

SEO Optimization

Add meta title, description, canonical tags

Include Open Graph + Twitter Cards

robots.txt and sitemap.xml must be present

Add favicon and Apple touch icon

Use schema.org structured data

Analytics & Tracking

Google Analytics 4

Optionally: Facebook Pixel (commented), Hotjar, Google Tag Manager

Forms & Interactivity

All forms must have input validation

Use send.php, Formspree, or ConvertKit

Add Thank You message or redirect

Optional: reCAPTCHA or honeypot

